# RTK - Rust Token Killer (Cline)

**Usage**: Token-optimized CLI proxy for shell commands.

## Rule

Always prefix shell commands with `rtk` to minimize token consumption.

Examples:

```bash
rtk git status
rtk cargo test
rtk ls src/
rtk grep "pattern" src/
rtk find "*.rs" .
rtk docker ps
rtk gh pr list
```

## Meta Commands

```bash
rtk gain              # Show token savings
rtk gain --history    # Command history with savings
rtk discover          # Find missed RTK opportunities
rtk proxy <cmd>       # Run raw (no filtering, for debugging)
```

## Why

RTK filters and compresses command output before it reaches the LLM context, saving 60-90% tokens on common operations. Always use `rtk <cmd>` instead of raw commands.

---

# Headroom - Context Optimization Layer

**Usage**: Context compression and token optimization for AI agents.

## Available Tools

Headroom is installed and available. Use these commands for additional optimization:

```bash
headroom proxy              # Start optimization proxy (port 8787)
headroom diff               # Structural diff (difftastic)
headroom sg                 # AST-aware search/replace (ast-grep)
headroom loc                # Fast lines-of-code / repo shape probe
headroom memory list        # List stored memories
headroom memory stats       # Memory statistics
headroom perf               # Analyze proxy performance
headroom learn              # Learn from past failures
```

## Proxy Mode (for supported agents)

For agents that support custom API URLs (Claude Code, Codex, Aider):
```bash
# Start proxy
headroom proxy --port 8787

# Then launch agent with:
# ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8787 claude
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8787/v1 <agent>
```

## Note

Headroom provides additional compression beyond RTK:
- SmartCrusher (JSON compression)
- CodeCompressor (AST-aware code compression)
- Kompress-v2-base (text compression model)
- CacheAligner (KV cache optimization)
- CCR (reversible compression with retrieval)
- Cross-agent memory

For Cline, RTK handles shell output compression. Headroom is available for
advanced use cases (proxy mode, memory, code analysis).